<dl id="n01034j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01034j">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01034j"> 34(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 100.000 edible snails used / yearly in London to glaze / pastry &amp; thicken / mock turtle soup</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Review of <cite>Animal Curiosities</cite> by W.S. Berridge]</font> One comes, for example, upon such items as the fact that <mark>a hundred thousand edible snails are used annually in London</mark> restaurants, mostly for <mark>glazing pastry and thickening mock turtle soup</mark> <small> <a name="IT17nov22" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IT17nov22"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (17 November 1922) 4/6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05112j" href="c05all.htm#c05112j">VI.C.05:112(j)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
